# Smart Calendar AI - Environment Variables

# ============================================================================
# FIREBASE SETUP (Required for database persistence)
# ============================================================================
# 1. Create a Firebase project at https://console.firebase.google.com
# 2. Create a Firestore database in test mode
# 3. Go to Project Settings > Service Accounts > Generate New Private Key
# 4. Copy the entire JSON and paste below (single line, no quotes)
# The JSON should contain: type, project_id, private_key, client_email, etc.
#
# IMPORTANT: Paste the ENTIRE service account JSON on one line (all on line below)
FIREBASE_SERVICE_ACCOUNT={"type":"service_account","project_id":"your-project-id","private_key_id":"..."}

# ============================================================================
# AI PARSING (Optional - uses regex fallback if not set)
# ============================================================================
# For Anthropic Claude (recommended):
ANTHROPIC_API_KEY=your_anthropic_api_key_here

# Or for OpenAI GPT:
# OPENAI_API_KEY=sk-...

# ============================================================================
# SECURITY NOTES
# ============================================================================
# - Do NOT commit `.env.local` to git (already in .gitignore)
# - Never share the Firebase service account JSON or API keys
# - Keys are read server-side and never exposed to the browser
# - For production, set up proper Firestore security rules
